gurmukhi: ckRq cwr ckÍY ckRq cau kuMt cv`gn ]
transliteration: Chakrat Chaar Chakravai Chakrat Chau Kount Chavaggad||
translation: Visualizing the Beauty of the Universal monarch all the four directions seem stunned.

gurmukhi: kot sUr sm qyj qyj nhI dUn cv`gn ]
transliteration: Kot Soor Sam Tej Ten Nahidoon Chavaggad||
translation: He hath the light of millions of suns, nay, even the light is two four times.

gurmukhi: kot cMd c`k prY qu`l nhI qyj ibcwrq ]
transliteration: Kot Channd Chakk Darai Tull Nahitej Bichaarat||
translation: A million moons are astonished to fine their light very dim as compared to His Light.

gurmukhi: ibAws prwsur bHm Byd nih byd aucwrq ]
transliteration: Biaas Paraasur Brahm Bhed Nah(i) Bed Ouchaarat||
translation: Vyas, Parshar, Brahma and Vedas cannot describe His mystery.

gurmukhi: swhwn swh swihb suGr Aiq pRqwp suMdr sbl ]
transliteration: Saahaan Saah Saahib Soughar At(i) Prataap Soundar Sabal||
translation: He is the king of kings, the Lord of Wisdom, Supremely Glorious, Beautiful and Powerful.

gurmukhi: rwjwn rwj swihb sbl Aimq qyj A`CY ACl ]8]39]
transliteration: Raajaan Raaj Saahib Sabal Amit Tej Achchai Achhal||8||39||
translation: He is the monarch of monarchs, the Lord of the Mighty having Unlimited Splendour, Unassailable and without deceprion.8.39.

gurmukhi: gihE jo n jwie so Agwh kY kY gwhIAqu CyidE jo n jwie so ACyd kY pCwnIAY ]
transliteration: Gadio Jo Na Jaae So Agadh Kai Kai Gadheeat(u) Chhedio Jo Na Jaae So Ached Kai Pachhaadeeai||
translation: He, who cannot be grasped, He is called Inaccessible and He, who cannot be assailed is recognized as unassailable.

gurmukhi: gMijE jo n jwie so AgMj kY kY jwnIAqu BMijE jo n jwie so ABMj kY kY mwnIAY ]
transliteration: Gadjio Jo Na Jaae So Agadj Kai Kai Jaaneeat(u) Bhanjio Jo Na Jaae So Abhanj Kai Kai Maaneeai||
translation: He who cannot be destroyed is known as indestructible and He, who cannot be divided in considered as indivisible.

gurmukhi: swiDE jo n jwie so AswiD kY kY swD kir CilE jo n jwie so ACl kY pRmwnIAY ]
transliteration: Saadhio Jo Na Jaae So Asaadh(i) Kai Kai Saadh Kar(i) Chhalio Jo Na Jaae So Achhal Kai Pramaaneeai||
translation: He, who cannot be disciplined, may be called incorrigible and He, who cannot be deceived is considered as Undeceivable.

gurmukhi: mMqR mY n AwvY so AmMqR kY kY mwnu mn jMqR mY n AwvY so AjMq kY kY jwnIAY ]1]40]
transliteration: Mantra Mai Na Aavai So Amanndra Kai Kai Maan(u) Man Jantra Main A Aavai So Ajantra Kai Kai Jaaneeai||1||40||
translation: He, who is without the impact of mantras (incantations) may be considered as Unspellable and He, who is without the impact of Yantras (mystical diagrams) may be known as Unmagical.1.40.
